OL,6,F"I don't want to give the impression
OL,7,Fthat I see myself as a victim. I can
OL,8,Fpass as white, therefore I don't
OL,9,Fexperience the abuse that non-white
OL,10,Fpeoples experience everyday.
OL,12,F"Having said that, it's still not
OL,13,Facceptable that we see acts of
OL,14,Fantisemitism at any point, and
OL,15,Fparticularly in the wake of one of the
OL,16,Fworst tragedies ever to happen to the
OL,17,FJewish people since 1945 and even
OL,18,Fbefore Israel had responded.
OL,20,F"If we can't express sympathy for the
OL,21,Fvictims, what have we got?", he added.
