OL,6,FNathan says his experience is that
OL,7,Fthere is no nuance to the debate over
OL,8,FIsrael and Gaza, and instead Jews are
OL,9,Fforced to pick a side between the
OL,10,FIsraeli government, or the Palestinian
OL,11,Fpeople, rather than being able to take
OL,12,Fwhat he considers to be a more
OL,13,Fbalanced view.
OL,15,F"It's perfectly acceptable I think to
OL,16,Fsay 'bring the hostages home but
OL,17,FIsrael's response is heavy-handed'",
OL,18,Fthe professor said, "but in the
OL,19,Fcurrent climate we're expected to take
OL,20,Fa side and therefore deny the pain and
OL,21,Fsuffering of the other side".
